# Keep the docker build context small. The biggest contributors
# to a naive `docker build .` are:
#   - target/        — cargo build artifacts (multi-GB)
#   - .git/          — full history (~hundreds of MB)
#   - examples/actors/<*>/target/ — PVM build artifacts
#   - zkpvm/target/  — zkVM build artifacts
#
# The image only needs source + the bundled PVM blobs at
# vosx/blobs/, so this list is generous with what to exclude.

# ── Build artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────
target/
**/target/
**/*.rlib
**/*.rmeta

# ── Git history + dev metadata ─────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.github/

# ── Editor + OS clutter ────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/*.swp

# ── Test fixtures we don't need at build time ──────────────────
examples/data/
examples/wasm/*/target/
zkpvm/STWO_MERKLE_LIFTED_OOB_ISSUE_DRAFT.md

# ── Existing container outputs ─────────────────────────────────
containers/tests/output/

# ── Big checked-in PDFs the workspace happens to carry ─────────
*.pdf

# ── Bench + perf datasets ──────────────────────────────────────
**/benches/data/

# Note: we DO want `vosx/blobs/` in the build context so
# build.rs's shipped-path fallback works.
